
				                 ER24 paramedics were returning to their branch when they came across the scene at 7.40am, ER24 spokesman Russel Meiring said.
“Upon closer inspection, paramedics found the man lying on the side of the road surrounded by members of a local security company. Paramedics assessed the man and found that he had sustained a gunshot wound to his buttock, leaving him in a serious condition.”
The man was treated for his wound and provided with pain-relief medication before he was transported to Addington Provincial Hospital under police supervision. The details surrounding the incident were not yet known, Meiring said.
– African News Agency (ANA)
